    "description": "In the introductory essay for Map 41 of the Barrington Atlas published in the Map-by-Map Directory, Vico Pancellorum is mentioned as a toponym with likely ancient origins, but absent is any specific evidence to that effect. Vico Pancellorum is a small Tuscan village located in the Province of Lucca. It is situated at 630 meters above sea level at the foot of Balzo Nero.",
